>problem:
>consider the following series of math operations:
>given a=b, then
>a2=b
>a2-b2=ab-b2
>(a+b)(a-b)=b(a-b)
>(a+b)=b
>a+a=a (all numbers with 2 above here are squared, not multiplied a 
>squared=a2)
>2a=a
>2=1
>Describe the operational rule that was preformed at each of the seven 
>lines. This "apparently" proves that 2=1, which we know is false. 
>Find what is wrong here.
>
